<paragraph id="E07536B6FE96FEF05889FB96FA236590" blockId="347.[151,1436,834,1257]" pageId="347" pageNumber="348">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE96FEF05914FB96FDB3654C" author="Rondani, C." box="[266,512,1050,1077]" pageId="347" pageNumber="348" pagination="193 - 231" refId="ref369428" refString="Rondani, C. (1865 c) Diptera italica non vel minus cognita descripta vel annotata observationibus nonnullis additis. Fasc. II. Muscidae. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 8, 193 - 231." type="journal article" year="1865">Rondani (1865c: 204)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE96FEF05A67FB96FCC4654C" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1865" box="[633,887,1051,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Platychyra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="347" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE96FEF05A67FB96FCC4654C" box="[633,887,1051,1077]" italics="true" pageId="347" pageNumber="348">Platychyra brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from just the male sex, without specifying either the 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE96FEF058ECFBB2FEFB6520" box="[242,328,1087,1113]" family="Number" pageId="347" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or the length of the specimens. He spelled the species as “ 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE96FEF05BF5FBB2FBDB6520" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1865" box="[1003,1128,1087,1113]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Platychyra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="347" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE96FEF05BF5FBB2FBDB6520" box="[1003,1128,1087,1113]" italics="true" pageId="347" pageNumber="348">brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” in his key (p. 202) but as “ 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE96FEF058CAFBEEFEE26504" box="[212,337,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="347" pageNumber="348">brevicanda</emphasis>
” in his description (p. 204). Acting as First Revisers (according to I.C.Z.N. 1999: Article 24.2.3), we here select “ 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE96FEF05962FB0AFE4A65D8" box="[380,505,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="347" pageNumber="348">brevicanda</emphasis>
” as an incorrect original spelling. We found 
<specimenCount id="F6CCFD3FFE96FEF05BEBFB0AFBCF65D8" box="[1013,1148,1159,1185]" pageId="347" pageNumber="348" type="generic" typeStatus="syntype">one syntype</specimenCount>
in this study. The MZUF also contains a (non-type) female numbered “527”. Rondani described this nominal species under the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE96FEF05914FB5DFE306591" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1859" box="[266,387,1232,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Platychyra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="347" pageNumber="348" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE96FEF05914FB5DFE306591" box="[266,387,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="347" pageNumber="348">Platychyra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is an “unjustified emendation of 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE96FEF05B5FFB5DFBD36591" authority="Rondani, 1856" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[833,1120,1232,1256]" genus="Platychira" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="347" pageNumber="348" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE96FEF05B5FFB5DFC066591" box="[833,949,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="347" pageNumber="348">Platychira</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE96FEF05BA2FB5DFBD36591" author="Rondani, C." box="[956,1120,1232,1256]" pageId="347" pageNumber="348" refId="ref368338" refString="Rondani, C. (1856) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: I. Genera italica ordinis dipterorum ordinatim disposita et distincta et in familias et stirpes aggregata. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 226 pp. + [2] pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1856">Rondani, 1856</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
” (
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE96FEF05C66FB5CFA306590" author="O'Hara, J. E. &amp; Cerretti, P. &amp; Pape, T. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L." box="[1144,1411,1231,1257]" pageId="347" pageNumber="348" pagination="1 - 268" refId="ref361577" refString="O'Hara, J. E., Cerretti, P., Pape, T. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (2011) Nomenclatural studies toward a world list of Diptera genus-group names. Part II: Camillo Rondani. Zootaxa, 3141, 1 - 268. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3141.1.1" type="journal article" year="2011">
O’Hara 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE96FEF05CCDFB5CFAB96591" box="[1235,1290,1232,1256]" italics="true" pageId="347" pageNumber="348">et al.</emphasis>
2011: 147
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
